"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/68ec836e-5a2a-a69c-107c-9458daaeb870.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:298px;width:298px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-778\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b778\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>🌟 Welcome to The Brew Shop, <strong>Moia</strong> <strong>Sparkling Water</strong>! Locally crafted by brother + sister duo, Farris and Raihan, Moia is the first ever middle eastern sparkling water brand bringing you the culture 🌙 vibes ✨ of Marrakech and Kabul and everything else in between, all conveniently in sparkling water form!<br><br>🌟 Find Moia cold as single cans in our mini-fridge on the front counter and in 12-packs ready to share!</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td><td id=\"mceColumnId-782\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b780\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/2fff02fe-c052-8dd3-efe0-a540ca8888e6.jpg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/2fff02fe-c052-8dd3-efe0-a540ca8888e6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:298px;width:298px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-781\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b781\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span><span><span><img src=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/e/notoemoji/17.0/2620_fe0f/72.png\" alt=\"☠️\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></span></span></span></span> <strong>Adroit Theory </strong>dropping in tomorrow<br>• <strong>Necrosynth</strong> Quadruple Hazy IPA with Citra, El Dorado, Mosaic &amp; Amarillo<br>• <strong>Death of Civilization in Slow Motion I. </strong>Hazy IPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; El Dorado<br>• <strong>Death.Net </strong>West Coast IPA with Citra, Strata &amp; Chinook<br>• <strong>Midnight Special </strong>Russian Imperial Stout</p><p>*expected Friday*</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b734\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-733\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b733\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Hot Crowler &amp; Growler Fills<p>Halfway Crooks Var Czech Pilsner</p><p>Brainstorm Let Him Cook Hazy IPA</p><p>Schilling Jelen Czech Dark Lager</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b599\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b579\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/4b34f2f5-1740-3ac1-e018-9f75d51e4db8.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/4b34f2f5-1740-3ac1-e018-9f75d51e4db8.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-723\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b723\"><table id=\"section_ce1f32e1838c124d31472aa1417ad4c3\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--39\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-22\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--50\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b722\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-721\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-580\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b580\"><table><tbody><tr><td><span>New wines in the door!</span><p><strong><span>Fantini Lava Campania Falanghina:</span></strong><span><span><span><span>Falanghina is one of Italy's great comeback stories — nearly lost to extinction in the mid-20th century when growers ripped out their vines in favor of more fashionable varieties. We're glad Falanghina made a comeback! Fantini Lava Falanghina comes from Campania's volcanic soils, shaped by ancient eruptions and rich in ash, pumice, and mineral deposits — all of which give the wine its signature sense of place. Think citrus blossom, ripe pear and a whisper of volcanic minerality that ties it all together.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span><span><span><span>Field Recordings Shucks</span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>: We are just a little bit obsessed with Andrew Jones' new release and ultimate \"oyster wine,\" Shucks. Crisp with saline-laced texture and notes of wet stone, zippy green apple and lemon-infused acidity. With 100% ocean vibes, this bottle is indeed built for pairing with shellfish.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>SoHu Orange Wine (returns!): </span></strong><span><span><span><span>We've been hotly anticipating the return of this orange wine from SoHu. Expectations were exceeded with lively, fresh peach and apricot paired with orange blossom. Easily quaffable and loveable. Hand Harvested, Native Yeast</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b724\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b416\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/18514262-187e-64ca-4c85-30bd91fdc6bf.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/18514262-187e-64ca-4c85-30bd91fdc6bf.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-415\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b415\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Wine we’re drinking this week:<p>We're rolling into one of the biggest weekends of the year where we have the delightful collision of Taylor Swift's wedding and America's 250th birthday. I personally can't think of a better reason to raise a glass. My pick for this celebratory, hot as hell weekend is <strong>Born Rambla Rose</strong>.<br><br>It's probably no surprise that we love supporting other women-owned businesses. Born Rose comes to us from a group of women from Barcelona who were so passionate about rosé that they pooled their energy and savings and built a winery that exclusively produces Rose. Among the all pink line-up of still and sparkling Roses, we fell for the serious, but crush worthy Rambla Rose which is of course named for Barcelona's most famous boulevard — a living, breathing, permanently sun-drenched promenade where the city does its best showing off.<br><br>Born Rambla Rose is made with 60% Garnacha and 40% Tempranillo, grown organically and fermented in stainless steel tanks to preserve the grapes' natural freshness and aroma. Grenache brings the sun-drenched Mediterranean fruit and floral aromatics; Tempranillo adds structure and a grounding earthiness. Pouring ballet pink with notes of peach, strawberry, citrus and a dry, mineral-tinged finish. And like all of Born Rosé's wines, Rambla Rose is 100% organic and clocks in with a low alcohol level - so go ahead and pour yourself a second glass. As an added bonus, Rambla Rose has a patio friendly screw cap which is perfect for this long holiday weekend of celebration.</p><p><em><span><span><span><span>This week’s writeup is brought to you by Beth.</span></span></span></span></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b508\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-452\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b452\"><table id=\"section_d099f2e64bc9b4b01f67bbbace5d5eca\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--33\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-10\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--44\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b456\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-455\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b453\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/8dc66e9b-7305-c0d1-5572-f12ee7415bed.jpeg\" width=\"534\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/8dc66e9b-7305-c0d1-5572-f12ee7415bed.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"533.8\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:533.8px;width:533.8px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-454\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b454\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span>July Tasting Events coming your way!</span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b457\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-177\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b177\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Thanks for your business! See you soon, Beth, Julie &amp; Aidan and the entire Brew Crew</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]><table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"660\" style=\"width:660px;\"><tr><td><![endif]--><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--31\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b9\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--6\"><table><tbody><tr></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b15\"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody></table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>",
